//   Public Interface ≈ Public APIs [Reserved: no exports]

// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Configuration Structure Map - Internal Organization
// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Go Workspace Directive Types:
//   go [version]      - Minimum Go version for workspace
//   use [path]        - Include a module in this workspace
//   replace [...]     - Workspace-wide dependency overrides
//
// Module Categories:
//   Core Modules      - Primary application and libraries
//   Supporting        - Utilities, tools, helpers
//   Local Overrides   - Forked/patched dependencies
//
// Organization Pattern:
//   - Core modules first (main application, primary libraries)
//   - Supporting modules second (utilities, tools)
//   - External local modules last (forked dependencies)

// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Helpers/Utilities
// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// [Reserved: Declarative config - go.work is a workspace manifest with no
// helper functions. The go toolchain provides all necessary operations:
//   go work sync   - Synchronize dependencies
//   go work use    - Add module to workspace
//   go work edit   - Edit workspace programmatically]

// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Configuration Content - Core Data
// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Module inclusions defining this workspace's scope.
// Each 'use' directive includes a module in the workspace.
//
// Extension Point:
// To add a new module to this workspace:
//   1. Ensure the module has a valid go.mod file
//   2. Add 'use ./path/to/module' below
//   3. Run 'go work sync' to update dependencies
//   4. Update METADATA "What This Coordinates" section

// ═══ Workspace Modules ═══

use (
	// --- Core Modules ---
	// Primary application and library modules.
	// [./path/to/main-app]     // [Brief purpose]
	// [./path/to/core-lib]     // [Brief purpose]

	// --- Supporting Modules ---
	// Utility and tool modules.
	// [./path/to/tools]        // [Brief purpose]

	// --- Local Overrides ---
	// Local versions of external dependencies (for development/patches).
	// [./local/forked-dep]     // [Why forked - what's different]
)

// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Error Handling
// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// [Reserved: Declarative config - go.work validation occurs via toolchain.
// The go toolchain handles all error detection:
//   - Invalid paths: Reported by go work sync
//   - Missing modules: Detected at build time
//   - Version conflicts: Resolved by workspace MVS
// No custom error handling in the workspace file itself.]

// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Public Interface
// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// [Reserved: Declarative config - go.work has no exported functions.
// The workspace file defines module coordination, consumed by:
//   - Go toolchain (go build, go test across modules)
//   - IDE integrations (gopls workspace support)
// The "interface" is the set of modules included in the workspace.]

